Hawks signed free agent PF Josh Powell, formerly of the Lakers, to a one-year, $1.1 million contract.
Chase Budinger returned from an ankle injury and missed all six of his shots, failing to score in 14 minutes.
As expected, 76ers guard Evan Turner will move to a bench role vs. the Hawks on Friday.
DeMarcus Cousins double-doubled with 17 points and 11 rebounds on Saturday, hitting 6-of-14 shots from the field to go with a block.
Johan Petro started in place of Brook Lopez (rest) and had eight points, seven rebounds and two blocks in Wednesday's loss to the Celtics.
Danilo Gallinari hit just 2-of-6 shots in 23 minutes for four points in Saturday's loss to the Hawks.
Updating an earlier item, Reggie Evans will have surgery on his fractured foot on Thursday.
Rudy Fernandez failed to score in six minutes before leaving Friday's game after being kicked in the groin.
Ronnie Price returned from a wrist injury and had six points in 11 minutes.
Luc Richard Mbah a Moute started again for the Bucks on Wednesday and had 10 points and nine rebounds in a loss to the Cavs.
Sebastian Telfair is still dealing with plantar fasciitis.
Antonio McDyess scored seven points on 2-of-3 shooting with five rebounds and four blocks in 22 minutes off the bench on Monday.
Josh Childress, who is just 0-of-4 from downtown this season, may soon play some PF off the Suns bench.
Leandro Barbosa hit 7-of-12 shots and two 3-pointers for 22 points and two steals in Friday's win.
Jason Terry scored just six points in the Mavs' blowout win on Monday, hitting 2-of-7 shots from the field with no other statistics in 21 minutes.
Thabo Sefolosha started and played 23 minutes, but didn't score and managed just three rebounds, two assists and a steal.
Chris Wilcox, who injured his hamstring during the preseason, is expected to make his season debut Sunday against the Kings.
Courtney Lee scored 13 points with six rebounds, three assists, and two steals while hitting 4-of-13 shots from the field on Monday.
James Posey is expected to be Josh McRoberts' backup at power forward.
Hakim Warrick came to life with 26 points off the bench on Sunday, making 10-of-13 FGs and 6-of-10 FTs, with six rebounds and two assists.
Jason Kidd scored 16 points on 6-of-8 shooting (including three 3-pointers) with eight rebounds, six assists, and a steal on Monday.
